message.content:
We first “anchor” on the starting fixed assets from the initial transaction. In our data the “Fixed Assets” row on 2023‑12‑31 gives an initial value of 5,000,000.00.

Then we scan for transactions that add to fixed assets – these are the “Fixed Assets Purchase” entries. We found four such lines with amounts as follows:
• 73,907.19  
• 171,448.09  
• 92,277.65  
• 191,303.24  

Adding these we get:  
73,907.19 + 171,448.09 = 245,355.28  
245,355.28 + 92,277.65 = 337,632.93  
337,632.93 + 191,303.24 = 528,936.17

So the total additions from purchases are 528,936.17.

Next we look for depreciation recorded against fixed assets. We see one “Depreciation” entry of 45,749.47 which will reduce the fixed asset net value.

Thus the net fixed assets at the end of the period become:
  Initial 5,000,000.00  
  + Purchases 528,936.17 = 5,528,936.17  
  – Depreciation 45,749.47 = 5,484,186.70

Presenting our answer in the required JSON format:

------------------------------------------------

{
  "solution": {
    "fixed assets net Initial Value": "5000000.00",
    "fixed assets net End Value": "5484186.70"
  }
}
